Employment at


BECOME THE KEY INGREDIENT!

The Key Ingredient that defines BRAVO | BRIO Restaurant Group (BBRG) is not just the dazzling decor in our stunning restaurants. It isn't only the bowl of Rigatoni Alla Bolognese that warms your belly on a cold evening or the crisp glass of Pinot Grigio enjoyed on the terrace in July. The Key Ingredient is each Team Member who each day creates a hospitable environment reminiscent of a Sunday afternoon gathering with friends and family. We want YOU to be that Key Ingredient. 


We are always interested in talking to potential Team Members who have a heart and a passion for hospitality. With new restaurants opening across the United States, opportunities exist from Hourly to Management positions. We take great pride in our quality training and development programs, creating leaders in the industry.

Visit our Career sites at:


BRAVO 

BRIO 


BON VIE 

Our fresh benefits and culture will entice you. Charitable CompassionAt BBRG, we believe that family is the key to happiness. We partner with national charities such as: No Kid Hungry - Share our Strength, Make-A-Wish Foundation, Children's Miracle Network, and The Ronald McDonald House Charities. On a local level, each restaurant is an engrained community partner and is encouraged to give back! Commitment to ExcellenceSo what makes that Sunday at Grandma's so special? The hospitality. We remain committed to providing the best possible experience for our Guests by taking ownership of our product, our Team Members and our culture. BBRG serves spectacular culinary creations while empowering our Team to create unique and pleasurable experiences for each diner. When our Guests have an event, meeting, or celebration, we want them to remember BBRG because of the inviting service and warm hospitality, just like Grandma's house. Grow Your PassionWant to marry your love for food and people? Then you have found the ONE! Our culture encourages professional growth and we have successful systems to help YOU be your best! We proudly promote internally at all levels of Management. Nearly three out of four General Managers and Executive Chefs started with BBRG as Assistant Managers, Sous Chefs or hourly Team Members. Your path is up to you….because you are the Key Ingredient. Tasty BenefitsBesides scrumptious food, there are many other perks that put BBRG at the head of the class of employers such as: comprehensive medical, dental and vision insurances, life and disability insurances, 401K with a company match, paid time off, flexible spending accounts, dining discounts for you (and your family/friends), medical health plans and support, and gym membership discounts. And who could forget the best perk of all…our lively, team-focused, hospitality-first culture!Are you Noodling? Here are some answers to your questions. 
What concepts does BBRG 
operate?
		BRAVO | BRIO Restaurant Group operates 
BRAVO! Cucina Italiana, BRIO Tuscan Grille and Bon Vie Bistro. Founded in 1992 
by Rick & Chris Doody in	Columbus, OH, we currently operate in 
over 33 states and have over 115 restaurants nationwide. Check out locations!
		 What is the Management 
selection process like?
Our selection process involves multiple 
steps including several interviews (one via phone) and a visit to our restaurant 
location to observe a lunch or dinner shift. Depending on scheduling and 
availability, the process can take one week or it can take 30 days. But 
regardless of the outcome, we hope to remain connected with you for many years 
to come! Once I apply, what 
happens?You will receive a confirmation 
correspondence that our Talent Acquisition Team has received your 
application/resume. If there is a position for which you qualify, we do our best 
to contact you for an interview as quickly as possible! Should a position not 
match your qualifications or be available in your area, we will keep your resume 
handy for future opportunities. How do I join the home office team?Based in Columbus OH, we have offices here and in Cleveland OH. To check out our current career opportunities, please visit the Bravo careers page.     

 


